about.summary: Statistical processing backend for 'ggstatsplot', this package creates expressions with details from statistical tests. Currently, it supports only the most common types of statistical tests: parametric, nonparametric, robust, and bayesian versions of t-test/anova, correlation analyses, contingency table analysis.

name: r-statsexpressions
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.4.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-statsexpressions
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/statsExpressions_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/statsExpressions/statsExpressions_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 365eeea771738781616a07f38e1cab100c9d0661195dc27e669cad1878a0fd5f

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-boot
    - r-broomextra >=3.0.0
    - r-correlation >=0.2.0
    - r-dplyr
    - r-effectsize >=0.3.0
    - r-ez
    - r-ipmisc >=2.0.0
    - r-metafor
    - r-metaplus
    - r-purrr
    - r-rcompanion
    - r-rlang
    - r-tidybf >=0.2.0
    - r-tidyr
    - r-wrs2
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-boot
    - r-broomextra >=3.0.0
    - r-correlation >=0.2.0
    - r-dplyr
    - r-effectsize >=0.3.0
    - r-ez
    - r-ipmisc >=2.0.0
    - r-metafor
    - r-metaplus
    - r-purrr
    - r-rcompanion
    - r-rlang
    - r-tidybf >=0.2.0
    - r-tidyr
    - r-wrs2

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('statsExpressions')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('statsExpressions')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://indrajeetpatil.github.io/statsExpressions/, https://github.com/IndrajeetPatil/statsExpressions
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: "Statistical processing backend for 'ggstatsplot', this package creates expressions with details from statistical tests. Currently, it supports only the\
    \ most common types of statistical tests: parametric, nonparametric, robust, and bayesian versions of t-test/anova, correlation analyses, contingency table analysis."
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
